troller. If anything asks for the controller of an object that doesn\rquote t have a controller, use its owner instead.\par \par }\pard\plain \s26\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2701857 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid2701857 Controlling Another Player\rquote s Turn\par }\pard\plain \s27\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2701857 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid2701857 One card (Mindslaver) allows a player to control another player\rquote s turn. The controller of another player\rquote s turn makes all choices and decisions that player is allowed to make, or is told to make, during that turn by rules or by any objects. A player doesn\rquote t lose life due to mana burn while another player controls his or her turn. See rule 507, \ldblquote Controlling Another Player\rquote s Turn.\rdblquote \par \par }\pard\plain \s26\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid2701857 Converted Mana Cost\par }\pard\plain \s27\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid2701857 The converted mana cost of an object is the total amount of mana in its mana cost, regardless of color. If an object has no mana cost, its converted mana cost is 0. See rule 203, \ldblquote Mana Cost and Color.\rdblquote \par }\pard\plain \s28\ql \li400\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin400\itap0\pararsid2701857 \i\f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\insrsid2701857 Example:}{\insrsid2701857  An Air Elemental has a mana cost of \{3\}\{U\}\{U\} and a converted mana cost of 5.\par }\pard\plain \s27\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2701857 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid2701857 \par }\pard\plain \s26\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2701857 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid2701857 Convoke\par }\pard\plain \s27\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2701857 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs34\insrsid2701857 Convoke is a static ability that functions while the spell is on the stack. \ldblquote Convoke\rdblquote  means \ldblquote As an additional cost to play this spell, you may tap any number of untapped creatures you control. Each creature tapped this way reduces the cost to play this spell by \{1\} or by one mana of any of that creature\rquote s colors.\rdblquote  Using the convoke ability follows the rules for paying additional costs in rules 409.1b and 409.1f\endash h. }{\insrsid2701857 It can\rquote t reduce the cost to play a spell to less than 0. See rule 502.46, \ldblquote Convoke.\rdblquote \par \par }\pard\plain \s26\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid2701857 Copiable Values\par }\pard\plain \s27\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2701857 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid2701857 An object\rquote s \ldblquote copiable values\rdblquote  are the values that are printed on the object, as modified by other copy effects, plus any values set for face-down spells or permanents and any values set by \ldblquote comes into play as\rdblquote  abilities. Other effects (including type-changing effects) and counters are not copied. See rules 503.2 and 503.3.\par \par }\pard\plain \s26\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs2