ptional.\par }\pard \s27\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2701857 {\insrsid2701857      A spell\rquote s controller chooses targets (see rule 409.1d) for a kicker effect only if he or she declared the intention to pay the kicker cost for that effect. If the spell\rquote s controller declared that he or she wouldn\rquote t pay a particular kicker cost, he or she doesn\rquote t choose the targets for the effect associated with that kicker cost.\par \par }\pard\plain \s26\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid2701857 Land\par }\pard\plain \s27\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2701857 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid2701857 Land is a type. Lands aren\rquote t spells and don\rquote t go on the stack; they are simply played from the hand. The active player may play a land once each turn during his or her main phase when he or she has priority and the stack is empty. If an object is both a land and another type, it can only be played as a land. It can\rquote t be played as a spell. See rule 212.6, \ldblquote Lands.\rdblquote \par \par }\pard\plain \s26\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid2701857 Land Type\par }\pard\plain \s27\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid2701857 Land subtypes are always a single word and are listed after a long dash: \ldblquote Land \emdash  Locus, Land \emdash  Urza\rquote s Mine,\rdblquote  etc. Land subtypes are also called land types. Lands may have multiple subtypes. Note that \ldblquote basic,\rdblquote  \ldblquote legendary,\rdblquote  and \ldblquote no