gh the }{\i\insrsid2701857 Time Spiral}{\insrsid2701857  set, is as follows: Arcane.\par \par }\pard\plain \s26\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid2701857 Soulshift\par }\pard\plain \s27\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2701857 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid2701857 Soulshift is a triggered ability. \ldblquote Soulshift N\rdblquote  means \ldblquote When this permanent is put into a graveyard from play, you may return target Spirit card with converted mana cost N or less from your graveyard to your hand.\rdblquote \par \par }\pard\plain \s26\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid2701857 Source of an Ability\par }\pard\plain \s27\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2701857 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid2701857 The source of an ability is the object that generated it. See rule 402, \ldblquote Abilities,\rdblquote  and rule 200.7.\par \par }\pard\plain \s26\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid2701857 Source of Damage\par }\pard\plain \s27\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2701857 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid2701857 The source of damage is the object that dealt it. If an effect requires a player to choose a source of damage, he or she may choose a permanent, a spell on the stack (including one that creates a permanent), or any object referred to by an object on the stack (including a creature that assigned combat damage on the stack, even i